main event: Observers in Eaton, Ohio, reported seeing a bright starlike object for 20 minutes on November 6, 1968.
interesting points: The object was described as being similar to a turnking light,The observation lasted for 20 minutes,The observers reported the object was bright and starlike, No photos or visual evidence were provided with the report, The case was concluded as having insufficient data for evaluation.
witness description: Observers reported the sighting, including one confirmed witness.
